comment.narrative:
Support to awareness on of existing relevant legal and policy frameworks on gender and security sector reform;
- Support the development of Work-plan and budget for Gender offices for Security Institutions;
- Print and disseminate compendium to security sector institutions; Support the development of a simplify version of the compendium; facilitate workshops tor the dissemination of the compendium and toolkits;
- Support advance specialize training course for Gender officers base on the results of the capacity needs assessment of the gender advisors (taskforce) and security institutions;
- Support focus training on harassment and reporting mechanism, proposal writing and report writing for gender offices;
- Provide advisory and support to the gender offices for the development and review of ToRs, work plans and gender policies;
- Support the gender task force to identify and lobby for promotion and enrollment for females through conferences, award ceremonies;
- Organize course on career development and leadership for female security offices and managers

-	Trained the total of fifty (50) participants (24 males, and 26 females) on the existing relevant legal and policy frameworks on gender and security sector reform; 

-	Supported the two days Trainers of Trainees workshop on the dissemination of the compendium. 43 (28 female and 15 male) individuals of 10 security institution benefited from the training to enhanced their capacity for the roll-out and decentralize WPS agenda;

-	 Developed work-plans for gender units within 10 security institutions with the National Gender and Security Sector National Taskforce five years strategic plan with the objective of mainstreaming gender in national security;

-	Printed and disseminated the compendium to all 10 security sector institutions; Facilitated the development of training to simplify the compendium through a 3 days workshops held for the compendium dissemination of the compendium and toolkit;

-	Supported the advanced training of Gender officers - Fifty (50) personnel from 10 security institution (12males and 38 females) on the bases of the capacity needs assessment of the gender advisors (taskforce) and security institution. Courses include; 
•	Project Management
•	Human Resource Management
•	Logistics and Supply Chain Management
•	 Concept Note/Proposal Writing and Report Writing. 
-	Supported the Sexual Harassment and reporting mechanism training which was conducted by Civil Service Agency (CSA). The total of 45 (28 Females and 17 males) from 10 security institutions. 
-	Provided advisory to 10 gender units for the review of their ToRs, gender policies and workplan. All units were represented by gender heads, deputies, human resource personnel and support staff. A total of fifty persons (24 males and 26 females). 

-	Supported the monitoring activities of Gender units as well as providing technical support to the implementation of activities within the project. Gender advisors and Consultants serve as liaison between project team and senior managers of security institutions.
-	Organized course on career development and Leadership for female security offices and managers to advanced females leadership. Six Seven (67) females benefited from the training. Participants included Coordinators, Directors and support staffs age ranging from 17-55 years of various national security institutions.
